"52:48:5" : {s: 52, a: 48, w: 5, r: "عين", t: "بِأَعْيُنِنَا", l: "عَيْن", lc: 57, tl: "bi-aʿyuninā", lb: "চোখ ",e: "(are) in Our Eyes", b: "আমার নজরদারিতে", f: 4, rm: "to hurt in the eye, smite anyone with the evil eye, flow tears, become a spy. Aayan - to view, face. Ainun - eye, look, hole, but of a tree, spy, middle letter of a trilateral word, spring of water, chief, personage of a place. Ayan (pl. Inun): lovely, wide-eyed, lovely black eyed. Maiinun - water, spring."},
